    "The model is compiled using Huber loss as discussed in Sect. 4.3 and Adam(Adaptive Momentum) [42] optimizer.",
    "(7) L() = 1 N N ∑ i=1 (y i, f (X i;)) (8) ∇ (y i, f (X i;))Extreme Forecaster: The Extreme Value Forecaster leverages the Transformer architecture [43] for time series forecasting, specifically designed to focus on rare events or extreme values.",
    "Unlike traditional models, the Transformer's attention Fig. 3 NOA-LSTM Cell architecturemechanism allows it to dynamically adjust its focus based on the input sequence, making it particularly adept at capturing and predicting extreme values.",
    "This capability is crucial in scenarios where accurately forecasting rare events is paramount, such as in financial markets, anomaly detection, or natural disaster forecasting.",
    "The Extreme Value Forecaster's architecture consists of multiple attention layers that enable it to effectively learn and model the complex patterns associated with extreme values, leading to improved forecasting accuracy and robustness in extreme event prediction.Extreme value classifier: The Extreme Value Classifier is constructed using a Feed Forward Deep Neural Network (DNN) to identify and classify extreme values in time series data."
